TOKYO—Possible delays to Sprint Corp.’s planned merger with T-Mobile US Inc. threaten Sprint parent SoftBank Group Corp.’s ambition to invest in the world’s most valuable startups.
The merger between Sprint and T-Mobile, announced last year, would lower SoftBank’s large debt by taking taking tens of billions of dollars in Sprint debt off SoftBank’s balance sheet.
That would expand Tokyo-based SoftBank’s financing options to fuel an investment machine that already manages a $100 billion investment fund and holds a big stake...